I want to build a complete mesh import system exactly like Unreal Engine, where we can drag and drop mesh files (compatible with Three.js) into the Content Browser and automatically import the mesh, materials, textures, and animations. The system should support all Three.js compatible formats and show previews in the Content Browser.
IMPORTANT: Please consider the current architecture and what we've already implemented:

Actor system with components
Content Browser
Component system
Material/texture system
Animation system (needs to be built)
Project save/load system
JSON storage

The mesh importer should integrate seamlessly with all existing systems.

Core Concept (Unreal Engine Style)
Mesh Import Workflow:

Drag & drop mesh file into Content Browser (or use Import button)
System automatically detects file format
Imports mesh geometry, materials, textures, skeleton, animations
Creates asset files in Content Browser
Shows preview thumbnail
Can drag mesh from Content Browser into scene or onto actors
Animations are separate assets linked to skeleton

